<TITLE> OMS extended to all divisions </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 2 (bdnews24.com)Open-Market Sale of rice has been extended to all divisional headquarters after its launch last month in Dhaka and three labour-intensive districts, food minister Abdur Razzaque said on Tuesday. The newly formed Rangpur division will also be brought under the programme. Moreover, preparation of a list of at least 4,000 hard-core poor in every ward of the Dhaka city and around the country is underway, the minister told reporters on Tuesday after a high-level meeting at the secretariat. The listed people will get maximum 20kg of rice a month at the government determined price. The government resumed OMS of rice on Jan 20 at the rate of Tk 22 per kilogram in four labour-intensive districtsDhaka, Narayanganj, Narsingdi and Gazipur. The programme is being launched with the help of 25 dealers in every division to sell 25 tonnes of rice, the meeting decided, keeping provision of increasing the amount as needed. From Wednesday, the number of trucks selling rice in Dhaka will rise to 100 from 70, the minister added. The programme will be continued until the price of rice is stabilised, he said, adding that with the current government reserves, the OMS programme could be extended up to the end of the Boro season (Feb-April). bdn
